olive oil
2 potato
20 g butter
1 bunch spring onion
1 cucumber
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet mayonnaise
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 packet Chicken Drumstick Fillet
1 sachet Creole spice blend

• Bring a medium saucepan of lightly salted water to the boil. Cut potato into large chunks.
• Cook potato in boiling water until easily pierced with a fork, 15 minutes. Drain and return to the saucepan.
• Add the butter and grated Parmesan cheese, then lightly crush with a fork. Season to taste and cover to keep warm.

TIP: Peel the potato if you prefer!

• While the potato is cooking, combine Creole spice blend, a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt in a medium bowl. Add boneless chicken drumsticks and turn to combine.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a medium-high heat.
• Cook chicken, turning occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 10-14 minutes.

TIP: The spice blend will char slightly in the pan, this adds to the flavour!

• Meanwhile, thinly slice spring onion. Roughly chop cucumber.
• In a large bowl, combine shredded cabbage mix, baby spinach leaves, cucumber, 1/2 the spring onion and a drizzle of the white wine vinegar and olive oil.
• Toss to combine. Season to taste.

• Slice Creole chicken.
• Divide chicken, slaw and cheesy crushed potatoes between plates.
• Top with remaining spring onion.
• Serve with mayonnaise.